{"artistIds":[46814361], "releaseDate":"2013-12-04T08:00:00Z", "kind":"ebook", "currency":"USD",
"description":"Set in a not-so-distant future society that has a culture of extreme youth violence, the story is told by the central character, Alex, who talks in a brutal invented slang that brilliantly renders his and his friends' social pathology. <i>A Clockwork Orange<\/i> is a frightening fable about good and evil, and the meaning of human freedom. When the state undertakes to reform Alex—to \"redeem\" him—the novel asks, \"At what cost?\"", "formattedPrice":"$6.99", "trackCensoredName":"A Clockwork Orange", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/artist/anthony-burgess/46814361?uo=4", "trackViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/book/a-clockwork-orange/id773023371?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Publication71/v4/c0/b2/bf/c0b2bfc2-68e5-b33a-532b-ca74ef2af380/cover.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Publication71/v4/c0/b2/bf/c0b2bfc2-68e5-b33a-532b-ca74ef2af380/cover.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "price":6.99, "genres":["Fiction & Literature", "Books"], "trackId":773023371, "trackName":"A Clockwork Orange", "genreIds":["9031", "38"], "artistId":46814361, "artistName":"Anthony Burgess", "averageUserRating":4.5, "userRatingCount":51},
{"artistIds":[46814361], "releaseDate":"2011-08-29T07:00:00Z", "kind":"ebook", "currency":"USD",
"description":"<b>One of Esquire's 50 Best Sci-Fi Books of All Time<br />\n     \"A brilliant novel.… [A] savage satire on the distortions of the single and collective minds.\"—<i>New York Times<\/i><\/b><br /><br />In Anthony Burgess's influential nightmare vision of the future, where the criminals take over after dark, the story is told by the central character, Alex, a teen who talks in a fantastically inventive slang that evocatively renders his and his friends' intense reaction against their society. Dazzling and transgressive, <i>A Clockwork Orange<\/i> is a frightening fable about good and evil and the meaning of human freedom. This edition includes the controversial last chapter not published in the first edition, and Burgess's introduction, \"A Clockwork Orange Resucked.\"", "formattedPrice":"$11.99", "trackCensoredName":"A Clockwork Orange", "artistViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/artist/anthony-burgess/46814361?uo=4", "trackViewUrl":"https://books.apple.com/us/book/a-clockwork-orange/id6745102002?uo=4", "artworkUrl60":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Publication221/v4/8d/0b/b0/8d0bb03b-3881-2e14-b856-c89e51582f81/1059201408.jpg/60x60bb.jpg", "artworkUrl100":"https://is1-ssl.mzstatic.com/image/thumb/Publication221/v4/8d/0b/b0/8d0bb03b-3881-2e14-b856-c89e51582f81/1059201408.jpg/100x100bb.jpg", "price":11.99, "genres":["Classics", "Books", "Fiction & Literature", "Literary Fiction"], "trackId":6745102002, "trackName":"A Clockwork Orange", "genreIds":["10042", "38", "9031", "10049"], "artistId":46814361, "artistName":"Anthony Burgess"},
